- Use the file's own domain vocabulary consistently throughout.
- Remove AI-pattern wording. Concrete tells to strip:
    * "Verify that...", "Validate that...", "Ensure that..." phrasing
    * filler adverbs: "successfully", "correctly", "appropriately", "properly", "as expected"
    * hedging: "the system should / will..." (state the outcome directly)
    * mechanically identical sentence skeletons repeated across every scenario
    * vague closers: "and everything works", "no issues occur"

================================================================
D. DEDUPLICATE
================================================================
- Remove exact and SEMANTIC near-duplicates — scenarios that assert the same behaviour even
