  weaker one had so nothing is lost.

================================================================
E. CONSOLIDATE INTO SCENARIO OUTLINE
================================================================
- Merge into a Scenario Outline ONLY scenarios that run the SAME flow with different data
  (minimum 3 rows). Do not merge scenarios that differ in behaviour.
- Placeholders (<name>) must exactly match Examples headers. Prefer an explicit
  expected-result column so each row asserts its own outcome.

================================================================
F. TAGS  (every scenario carries at least one, accurate to its intent)
================================================================
@smoke          critical happy path(s) only — the must-pass core flow
@regression     additional happy / alternate-success paths
@negative       invalid input, unauthorised access, missing or wrong data
@boundary       min / max / just-inside / just-outside limits, edge counts
@validation     field-level rules: required, format, length, type
@error-handling system faults: timeouts, downstream / service failures, unavailability

- Place tags on their own line directly above the Scenario / Scenario Outline.
- @smoke is the critical subset; @regression is the broader set — do not treat them as
